Driver: It just depends on the rate. I don’t like going north because of Austin, Houston, and Waco traffic. I prefer South Texas lanes like Laredo, Corpus, Rio Grande Valley, Midland, and Odessa.
Driver: As long as it’s above $2 per mile, I’ll consider it. I already have enough work that I can skip loads if they’re not worth it.
Dispatch: We’ve actually booked the most loads in South Texas. We also see a lot going to Ohio, Oregon, Oklahoma, and Florida.
Driver: Maybe you can send me your website so I can take a look. I’d like to try a load or two, see how it works with my factoring company, and then go from there.
Dispatch: Have a good one.
Driver: Yes, sir.

